	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64637993"><p>Reminds me of high school days. A friend got a job maintaining a PDP-8 that controlled CNC machining equipment at a small factory.</p><p>Sometimes the PDP-8 would get wedged. The problem is that turning the power off and on didn't help because the wedged state was preserved in the magnetic core memory.</p><p>So he would rapidly cycle the power until a power glitch invalidated some of the memory, then the computer would crash and could be rebooted.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64637993">
