			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64638121"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64638121"><p>Someone upthread noted that the error was preserved through reboots - capacitor. There's a simple answer to that, which I learned from an on-site tech call: unplug your computer, *then* hit the start button, until there's no flash of light. You've now discharged the cap, and can plug it back in and boot.</p></div>
	</div>

